      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/3/88 ¶  ¶ The plant from the snowy mountains, ¶ SnowyMountains, NSW. ¶  ¶ dear Mr Deane, is Scleranthus biflorus; the little rubiaeceous weed is Sherardia arvensis, L., introduced from Britain or p...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.03.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Deane</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 581(a), folder 30, series 4, MS 610 Deane family papers, National Library of Australia, Canberra.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/3/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plant from the snowy mountains,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Snowy<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Mountains, NSW.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>dear Mr Deane, is Scleranthus biflorus; the little rubiaeceous weed is Sherardia arvensis, L., introduced from Britain or perhaps S. Europe</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have hardly the material for the plate of Acacia pruinosa complete; should you happen to pass the plant,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>kindly send of such rarity a little more.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had asked for fruiting specimens in M to H. Deane</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>23 February 2024; see notes thereto.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I fear, the tour during Easter, hoped for to Mt Seaview, will remain unaccomplished.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had been urging an expedition to Mt Seaview, in northern NSW, for some time; see, for example, M to Linnean Society of New South Wales, March 1887 (in this edition as 87-03-00c), and M to E. Ramsay, 18 March 1887.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>But see notes to M to H. Deane,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>12 October 1888, for M's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>already<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in 1884<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>urging<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>J. H. Maiden to visit.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Acacia pruinosa</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Scleranthus biflorus;</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sherardia arvensis</p>
